#OUTLIER  
import pandas as pd

def remove_outliers_iqr(df, columns):
    for col in columns:
        Q1 = df[col].quantile(0.25)
        Q3 = df[col].quantile(0.75)
        IQR = Q3 - Q1
        lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
        upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
        df = df[(df[col] >= lower_bound) & (df[col] <= upper_bound)]
    return df

columns_to_clean = ['age', 'Income','spending']

niilsen_data = remove_outliers_iqr(niilsen_data, columns_to_clean)

#Kmeans 
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

# 1.  
scaler = StandardScaler()
scaled_data = scaler.fit_transform(niilsen_data[['age', 'spending']])


inertia = []  
k_range = range(1, 11) 

for k in k_range:
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=42, n_init=10)
    kmeans.fit(scaled_data)
    inertia.append(kmeans.inertia_)  

#    Elbow method
plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
plt.plot(k_range, inertia, 'o-', color='teal', linewidth=2, markerfacecolor='orange')
plt.title('    Elbow ', fontsize=14, weight='bold')
plt.xlabel('  ')
plt.ylabel(' ')
plt.xticks(k_range)
plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

sns.set(style="whitegrid", palette="deep")
plt.rcParams['font.family'] = 'Helvetica'
plt.rcParams['axes.spines.top'] = False
plt.rcParams['axes.spines.right'] = False
plt.rcParams['axes.linewidth'] = 0.5

scaler = StandardScaler()
scaled_data = scaler.fit_transform(niilsen_data[['age', 'spending']])

# KMeans 
kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=3, random_state=42, n_init=10)
niilsen_data['Cluster'] = kmeans.fit_predict(scaled_data)
centroids_scaled = kmeans.cluster_centers_
centroids_original = scaler.inverse_transform(centroids_scaled)

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
palette = sns.color_palette("viridis", 3) 

sns.scatterplot(
    data=niilsen_data,
    x='age', y='spending',
    hue='Cluster', palette=palette,
    s=150, edgecolor='black', linewidth=1.2, alpha=0.8
)

plt.scatter(
    centroids_original[:, 0], centroids_original[:, 1],
    marker='*', s=500, c='red', label='Centroids', edgecolors='white', linewidths=2
)

for i, (x, y) in enumerate(centroids_original):
    plt.text(x, y + 1.8, f'Centroid {i+1}', ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold', color='black')
    
plt.title('Kmeans cluster', fontsize=18, fontweight='bold', pad=20)
plt.xlabel('', fontsize=15)
plt.ylabel('', fontsize=15)
plt.legend(title='Cluster', title_fontsize=14, fontsize=12, loc='upper right')
plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', linewidth=0.7, alpha=0.4)

plt.gca().set_facecolor('white')
plt.gca().patch.set_linewidth(1)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

#   
cluster_stats = niilsen_data.groupby('Cluster').agg(
    age_mean=('age', 'mean'),
    spending_mean=('spending', 'mean'),
    cluster_size=('Cluster', 'size')
).reset_index()

print(cluster_stats)

   Cluster   age_mean  spending_mean  cluster_size
0        0  53.819364     517.712428           692
1        1  33.284232     194.227178           964
2        2  38.877289    1437.684982           546

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

# 1.    (Income  Spending)
scaler = StandardScaler()
scaled_data = scaler.fit_transform(niilsen_data[['Income', 'spending']])  # Replace 'age' with 'income'

# 2.      inertia (  )- 
inertia = []  # Inertia-   
k_range = range(1, 11)  # k- 1- 10   

for k in k_range:
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=42, n_init=10)
    kmeans.fit(scaled_data)
    inertia.append(kmeans.inertia_)  #  k-  inertia- 

# 3. Elbow  
plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
plt.plot(k_range, inertia, 'o-', color='teal', linewidth=2, markerfacecolor='orange')
plt.title('   Elbow ', fontsize=14, weight='bold')
plt.xlabel('  (k)')
plt.ylabel('Inertia ( )')
plt.xticks(k_range)
plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=3, random_state=42, n_init=10)
niilsen_data['Cluster'] = kmeans.fit_predict(scaled_data)
centroids_scaled = kmeans.cluster_centers_
centroids_original = scaler.inverse_transform(centroids_scaled)

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
palette = sns.color_palette("viridis", 3)  

sns.scatterplot(
    data=niilsen_data,
    x='Income', y='spending', 
    hue='Cluster', palette=palette,
    s=150, edgecolor='black', linewidth=1.2, alpha=0.8
)

plt.scatter(
    centroids_original[:, 0], centroids_original[:, 1],
    marker='*', s=500, c='red', label='Centroids', edgecolors='white', linewidths=2
)

for i, (x, y) in enumerate(centroids_original):
    plt.text(x, y + 1.8, f'Centroid {i+1}', ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold', color='black')

plt.title('Customer Segmentation with KMeans Clustering', fontsize=18, fontweight='bold', pad=20)
plt.xlabel('Income', fontsize=15) 
plt.ylabel('Spending', fontsize=15)
plt.legend(title='Cluster', title_fontsize=14, fontsize=12, loc='upper right')
plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', linewidth=0.7, alpha=0.4)

plt.gca().set_facecolor('white')
plt.gca().patch.set_linewidth(1)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

cluster_stats = niilsen_data.groupby('Cluster').agg(
    income_mean=('Income', 'mean'),
    spending_mean=('spending', 'mean'),
    cluster_size=('Cluster', 'size')
).reset_index()

print(cluster_stats)

   Cluster   income_mean  spending_mean  cluster_size

1        1  31807.264768     103.578059           948

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler

# 1.    (Age  MntWines)
scaler = StandardScaler()
scaled_data = scaler.fit_transform(niilsen_data[['age', 'MntWines']])

# 2.      inertia- 
inertia = []
k_range = range(1, 11)

for k in k_range:
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=42, n_init=10)
    kmeans.fit(scaled_data)
    inertia.append(kmeans.inertia_)

# 3. Elbow 
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
plt.plot(k_range, inertia, 'o-', color='teal', linewidth=2, markerfacecolor='orange')
plt.title('    Elbow ', fontsize=14, weight='bold')
plt.xlabel('  (k)')
plt.ylabel('Inertia ( )')
plt.xticks(k_range)
plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', alpha=0.6)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# 4.  
kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=3, random_state=42, n_init=10)
niilsen_data['Cluster'] = kmeans.fit_predict(scaled_data)
centroids_scaled = kmeans.cluster_centers_
centroids_original = scaler.inverse_transform(centroids_scaled)

# 5. Scatter plot
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
palette = sns.color_palette("viridis", 3)

sns.scatterplot(
    data=niilsen_data,
    x='age', y='MntWines',
    hue='Cluster', palette=palette,
    s=150, edgecolor='black', linewidth=1.2, alpha=0.8
)

plt.scatter(
    centroids_original[:, 0], centroids_original[:, 1],
    marker='*', s=500, c='red', label='Centroids', edgecolors='white', linewidths=2
)

for i, (x, y) in enumerate(centroids_original):
    plt.text(x, y + 1.8, f'Centroid {i+1}', ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold', color='black')

plt.title('Customer Segmentation using Age and MntWines', fontsize=18, fontweight='bold', pad=20)
plt.xlabel('Age', fontsize=15)
plt.ylabel('Wine Spending (MntWines)', fontsize=15)
plt.legend(title='Cluster', title_fontsize=14, fontsize=12, loc='upper right')
plt.grid(True, linestyle='--', linewidth=0.7, alpha=0.4)
plt.gca().set_facecolor('white')
plt.gca().patch.set_linewidth(1)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# 6. Cluster statistics
cluster_stats = niilsen_data.groupby('Cluster').agg(
    mntwines_mean=('MntWines', 'mean'),
    age_mean=('age', 'mean'),
    cluster_size=('Cluster', 'size')
).reset_index()
